def: Wearing a turban. " A malignant and a turbaned Turk." Shak.
Act of enraging or state of being enraged; excitement. [Obs.]
Pertaining to, or like, a beast; brutal. [R.]Animal and belluine life. Atterbury.
Animals without a mouth or regular internal organs, as thesponges.
Pertaining to, or containing, gonidia or gonimia, as that partof a lichen which contains the green or chlorophyll-bearing cells.
The quality or state of being in peril; absence of safety;insecurity. Bacon.
To wrap the head of in a hood. [Obs.] Shak.
Of or pertaining to Anjou in France.-- n. A native of Anjou.
The lower part or basement of a building or pedestal; -- usedloosely for several different forms of basement.
